english_text: To make the earth safe for wildlife, even inzoos—especially if they become a final refuge—war, mankind's plague, must be eliminated.

yoruba_text: Bú omi tó mọ́ sí ọwọ́, kó o sì fiọṣẹsí i.
english_text: Wet your hands in clean running water and applysoap.

yoruba_text: Fífiọṣẹà ti omi tà bí eérú à ti omi fọwọ́ máa ń fọ à wọn kòkòrò à rùn kúrò lọ́wọ́ ẹni.
english_text: Washing them withsoapand water or ash and water removes germs.

yoruba_text: Fífiọṣẹà ti omi fọ ọwọ́ wa lè dènà à rùn ká sì ti pa bẹ́ẹ̀ gba ẹ̀mí wa là.
english_text: Washing the hands withsoapand water can prevent illness and actually save lives.

yoruba_text: A lè bá wọn mú aṣọ òtútù tó nípọn wá tà bí ká ra à wọn ohun ìlò bíọṣẹìwẹ̀, nǹkan ìpara à ti irú à wọn nǹkan bẹ́ẹ̀ wá fún wọn.
english_text: With the resident's well-being in mind, we could bring a warm dressing gown or a few personal-care products.
